section.section:
"Applicant" does not include:
a financial institution that has loaned money or extended financing for the acquisition, development, or construction of or improvements on the land that is the subject of an application;
a municipal or public corporation;
a public authority;
an electric company or electric supplier applying for a certificate of public convenience and necessity under § 7-207 or § 7-208 of the Public Utilities Article; or
a person that is hired or retained as an accountant, attorney, architect, engineer, land use consultant, economic consultant, real estate agent, real estate broker, traffic consultant, or traffic engineer.

text.section:
"Application" means:
an application for a zoning map amendment as part of a piecemeal or floating zone rezoning proceeding;
a formal application for a comprehensive map planning change or zoning change during the county comprehensive land use plan update;
an application for a map amendment to the county water and sewerage plan;
a request made under Article 23A, § 9(c) of the Code for the Board to approve the placement of annexed land in a zoning classification that allows a land use that is substantially different from the use for the land authorized in the zoning classification of the county applicable at the time of annexation; or
an application to create a district or easement or other interest in real property as part of an agricultural land preservation program.

"Business entity" means:
a sole proprietorship;
a corporation;
a partnership; or
a limited liability company.
